  "text": "To gain more diagnostic certainty, CSF was obtained by lumbar puncture. Amyloid-β 1−42 (Aβ [CITATION_1] ), total tau, and tau phosphorylated at threonine-181 (Ptau-181) were measured by sandwich ELISA (Innogenetics, Gent, Belgium) [CITATION_2] . CSF analyses were performed at the VUmc Department of Clinical Chemistry. Cut-off levels in our lab are as follows: Aβ 42 < 550, total tau > 375, and ptau > 52 [CITATION_3] . CSF was available for 140 subjects (SC: n=59; AD: n=62; FTD: n=19).",
